questions.question: What is the purpose of the ITIL service value system (SVS)?
options: To ensure value co-creation through integrated components
questions.explanation: The ITIL SVS describes how all components and activities work together to enable value co-creation.

questions.question: Which concept focuses on the benefits, usefulness, and importance of something?
questions.explanation: Value is the perceived benefits, usefulness, and importance of something.

questions.question: Which is NOT one of the four dimensions of service management?
questions.explanation: The four dimensions include suppliers and partners, not suppliers and budgets.

questions.question: What is an outcome in ITIL 4?
questions.explanation: An outcome is a result for a stakeholder enabled by one or more outputs.

questions.question: Which guiding principle recommends working iteratively with feedback?
questions.explanation: This guiding principle encourages incremental improvements and regular feedback.
